# Backend Integration Plan — Node.js + MongoDB

## Overview
Build a full REST API backend using **Node.js + Express + MongoDB (Mongoose)** and connect it to the existing React frontend. The demo mock data will be replaced by real API calls.

---

## Backend Folder Structure

```
chatgpt react/
├── ayursutra-react/          ← existing React frontend
└── ayursutra-backend/        ← NEW Node.js backend
    ├── server.js
    ├── .env
    ├── package.json
    ├── config/
    │   └── db.js             ← MongoDB connection
    ├── middleware/
    │   ├── auth.js           ← JWT verify middleware
    │   └── errorHandler.js
    ├── models/
    │   ├── User.js           ← Patient / Doctor / Admin
    │   ├── Appointment.js
    │   ├── Therapy.js
    │   ├── Invoice.js
    │   └── Feedback.js
    └── routes/
        ├── auth.js           ← /api/auth
        ├── users.js          ← /api/users
        ├── appointments.js   ← /api/appointments
        ├── therapies.js      ← /api/therapies
        ├── invoices.js       ← /api/invoices
        └── feedback.js       ← /api/feedback
```

---

## API Endpoints

### Auth — `/api/auth`
| Method | Route | Description |
|---|---|---|
| POST | `/register` | Register patient / doctor / admin |
| POST | `/login` | Login → returns JWT token |
| GET | `/me` | Get current user (token required) |

### Users — `/api/users`
| Method | Route | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/patients` | List all patients (admin/doctor) |
| GET | `/doctors` | List all doctors |
| PUT | [/:id](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#22-57) | Update user profile |
| DELETE | [/:id](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#22-57) | Delete user (admin) |

### Appointments — `/api/appointments`
| Method | Route | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/` | Get appointments (filtered by role) |
| POST | `/` | Book appointment |
| PUT | [/:id](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#22-57) | Update / reschedule |
| DELETE | [/:id](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#22-57) | Cancel |

### Therapies — `/api/therapies`
| Method | Route | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/` | Get therapies |
| POST | `/` | Add therapy |
| PUT | [/:id](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#22-57) | Update therapy |

### Invoices — `/api/invoices`
| Method | Route | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/` | Get invoices (doctor's own) |
| POST | `/` | Create invoice |
| PUT | [/:id](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#22-57) | Update invoice |
| DELETE | [/:id](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#22-57) | Delete invoice |

### Feedback — `/api/feedback`
| Method | Route | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/` | Get feedback |
| POST | `/` | Submit feedback |
| PUT | `/:id/reply` | Doctor reply to feedback |

---

## MongoDB Models

- **User**: `name, email, password (bcrypt), role (patient/doctor/admin), centre, speciality, phone, address`
- **Appointment**: `patientId, doctorId, type, date, duration, status, notes, centre`
- **Therapy**: `name, patientId, doctorId, sessions, completed, progress, startDate, endDate, status`
- **Invoice**: `invoiceNo, clinicName, patient, doctor, items[], subtotal, taxTotal, grandTotal, paymentStatus, paidAmount, signatureData, stampData, notes, isDraft`
- **Feedback**: `patientId, doctorId, content, rating, reply, date`

---

## Frontend Changes
Replace [mockData.js](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/data/mockData.js) usage with an **API service layer**:

- **`src/services/api.js`** — Axios instance with base URL + JWT interceptor
- **`src/services/authService.js`** — login, register, getMe
- **`src/services/appointmentService.js`**
- **`src/services/invoiceService.js`**
- **`src/services/feedbackService.js`**

[AuthContext.jsx](file:///c:/Users/het22/Downloads/chatgpt%20react/ayursutra-react/src/context/AuthContext.jsx) will be updated to call the real API instead of local DEMO_USERS array.

---

## Tech Stack
| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Backend | Node.js, Express.js |
| Database | MongoDB with Mongoose ODM |
| Auth | JWT (jsonwebtoken) + bcryptjs |
| CORS | cors middleware |
| Frontend HTTP | Axios |

---

## Verification Plan
1. Start MongoDB locally (or MongoDB Atlas connection)
2. Start backend: `npm start` in `ayursutra-backend/`
3. Test login API with Postman/browser
4. Confirm React frontend login works via real API
5. Test CRUD for appointments, invoices, feedback
